  "title": "A Star, a Gunslinger, and a Conspiracy",
  "summary": "At a CEC space station unveiling of a sleek new modified Corellian Corvette, Lord Geophreigh Smitherbodkins works the crowd, charming the Varvani chamberlain Mara Shinomiya while hosting the flamboyant holovid star Wynn Ryder and the grimy Corellian gunslinger Alac Y'All. Amid banter about the ship's hidden turbolasers and a teased luxury speeder called the Vanquish, Smitherbodkins gauges his guests' loyalties; Mara excuses herself to depart with a lovely Sarian singer, and Alac wanders off after admiring the ship's weapons. Smitherbodkins then lures Wynn to his private office, drops his affectations and exaggerated limp, and reveals his true purpose: he wants a sovereign Corellia, free of both the Empire and the New Republic. Wynn, a patriotic Corellian, agrees to infiltrate and lead the freedom-fighter movement to serve their shared aims, accepting records of Imperial movements to memorize and a meeting with the rebel commander, and the two seal their conspiracy with Wynn's parting cry of 'Corellia Forever.'",
